Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
auto_file_prefix(25.10)                                auto_file_prefix(25.10)

Name
       auto_file_prefix

Syntax
       auto_file_prefix

       Type: String

       Default: ""

       Specifies  a  prefix to be applied to all files 'auto-generated' by the
       tool. This includes report files or other  output  files  with  default
       names  that  are  automatically created by some commands in the current
       run directory. So a default name like "cmd.report" will  become  "<pre-
       fix>cmd.report".  Default  names  that have been overridden with a name
       chosen by the user, are not affected. This allows multiple simultaneous
       runs from the same run directory to direct default output files to dif-
       ferent locations to avoid collisions.

Related Information
              * auto_file_dir

